==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cortex
<hw>Cor"tex</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocir⟧r"t⟦ecr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Cortices</plw> <pr>(-t<?/-s<?/z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L., bark. Cf. <er>Cork</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Bark, as of a
tree; hence, an outer covering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Bark; rind; specifically, cinchona
bark.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The outer or superficial part of
an organ; <as>as, the <ex>cortex</ex> or gray exterior substance of the
brain</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cortical</ent>⟦br⟧
